          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">German and Yiddish</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <placeName>N.Y.</placeName>
                                        <date>Friday Pericofe <add>?</add></date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)"><del>(<date>December</date>)</del>
                                        <date>February 1849</date>.</p>
                              <p><addressee>Revd. Leeser</addressee>,
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">In the last number of the “Occident,”<lb/> I
                                        notice an article signed with the name “<persName>Ayala<lb/>
                                                  Sh'lucha</persName>” ( ). I also noticed my name
                                        mentioned<lb/> in an article in the last number of your
                                        valued<lb/> magazine, with the signature “Ayala
                                        Sh'lucha”<lb/> (in connection with this one may well add the
                                        closing<lb/> phrase, “Who gives forth beautiful words”)*.
                                        For<lb/> this mention I want to express my thanks to
                                        you<lb/> for your defense of me against the attacks in<lb/>
                                        certain <del>?</del> issues of the “Hasmonean”.<lb/> It was
                                        at this time that I first became<lb/> aware that you are the
                                        second one who did not<lb/> overlook <del>my</del> the
                                        insult to me. You were<lb/> good enough to send the number
                                        containing<lb/> your defense, whereas the first one who
                                        de-<lb/>fended me in the “Hasmonean,” signed with the<lb/>
                                        name “<persName>Ashkenazi</persName>,”still remains
                                        unknown<lb/> to me. Just why you as well the other
                                        fighter<lb/> preferred to remain unknown, I cannot<lb/>
                                        explain. The men of action and pious people<lb/> of old used
                                        to sign their names openly in<lb/> the course of a struggle.
                                        If I did not</p>
                              <p>*Genesis 49.21</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>thank you until now, it is because I was<lb/> afraid of hurting
                                        your feelings, but I have<lb/> always valued your attitude.
                                        That I want<lb/> you to know, since your magazine takes
                                        the<lb/> middle road as its tendency. I repeat what<lb/> I
                                        have once remarked to you that it<lb/> would be much more
                                        useful for your<lb/> magazine to be a weekly instead of
                                        a<lb/> monthly.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Along with this, I want to ask you<lb/> to include
                                        in the next number the following<lb/> notice, “Ethrogim and
                                        Lulabim From <placeName>Italy</placeName>,<lb/> as a Title,
                                        from <persName>C. Nussbaum</persName>, <placeName>187
                                                  Rivington<lb/> St.</placeName> are to be had
                                        Settrogim and lulabim<lb/> from
                                        <placeName>Italy</placeName>.</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <hi rend="underline">German Advertisement</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Double lines inserted here to divide letter from the
                                                  following</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">If you can send me your prayer-<lb/>books of the
                                        German ritual and the pentateuchs,<lb/> unbound at a low
                                        price, I should like to<lb/> order some from you. Please let
                                        me know the<lb/> exact price of the above, both cheaply
                                        and<lb/> elegantly bound.</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Respectfully,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">
                                        <persName role="author">C. Nussbaum</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Since I cannot obtain a number of<lb/> your magazine, please do not
                                        forget it<lb/> or put it aside, so that it might be
                                        left<lb/> out. If you would order something for me,<lb/> or
                                        use your influence in my favor,<lb/> I shall be obliged to
                                        you.</p>
                    </body>
